<br>
Anyone can buy up a character on ebay with the best gear imaginable.  What do you have?  Well, you've managed about 5 minutes of pleasure spending money and now you have a character that has nowhere to go and nothing to do because it's already all topped out.  Game over.<br>
<br>
Contrast this with leveling up yourself and you have 60 levels of fun grouping and then months and months of fun raiding.  At the end, what you have in your hand is the same as what the ebayer has.  What you have in your memory, the ebayer will never understand. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukolanistormynytes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KolaniStormynytes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 177<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/21/02 3:47:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1248.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ebay and integrity</span><hr size=1> There's a wurmy, 50kpp, and a Lodi Shell on playerauctions right now. Tempted? Yes. A chance I'd do it? None in hell. Despite that 50 kpp would provide the funds for grandmastering fletching. Despite that a wurmy is one of those weapons that I want badly. Despite that I want a Lodi Shell. I woudn't be able to look at my inventory screen. <p>Kolani - 
