class=m><span class=title>   Re: ebay and integrity</span><hr size=1> The arguments here in favor of not condemning ebayers seem to be:<br>
1) Everyone violates the EULA, so there is no possible judge and jury for EULA violations. Everyone should just do what they feel is right and allow others to do the same.<br>
<br>
2) It is not hurting you so stop condeming them.<br>
<br>
Now, these sound so nice and open minded who would not agree with them? I just happen to disagree with them. Lets say that we are talking about people who evade taxes, not like Enron, but just a single person. They claim more dependents, deductions, turn vacations into business trips. We wll know the ways. Now apply rules 1 and 2 to the situation. After all who is it hurting? They are not stealing from you and everyone cheats on their taxes.<br>
<br>
The problem is it does hurt you. Smaller revenues lead to tax increases down the road. Also, the IRS starts to assume that everyone cheats because all they see are cheats. Now when you get audited you will get that assumption applied to you, even if you are 100% honest.<br>
<br>
So how do ebayers hurt the general community? In my opinion there are direct hurts such as someone who does not know the class, does not know the community culture, does not understand local mores. A good solid player, however, can overcome these pretty easily. I understand that and can even accept that some people belive this enough to tolerate ebayers. <br>
<br>
My bigger problem is with the fact that people who buy and use ebay characters tend (note: tend does not mean 100%, it means many, but not all) to be the type of people who scoff at other rules. They tend to be the type who do not respect camps, believe that might makes right, demean and scoff at others who they believe are weaker than them. They tend to have the attitude that money can buy them the right to do what ever they want. So everytime a great high level player ebays his/her character we lose twice. The first time when the player leaves and the second time when a ebay-type person assumes the controls. <br>
<br>
Borm <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzarsissrazorscale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zarsiss Razorscale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 146<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/21/02 9:11:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1248.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ebay and integrity</span><hr size=1> Integrity doesn't have stats.  <p><CENTER>

