<br>
I'm not sure what your problem is but here are some things I have learned from dealings with two of the top guilds now.<br>
<br>
Uber DEFINATELY comes with a price. Now this price may<br>
be <br>
<br>
a) long hours at the keyboard<br>
b) having uber friends or multiple accounts and less time at the keyboard<br>
c) it may be $999.99 on Ebay. <br>
d) using exploits, cheats, etc...<br>
<br>
The point is, how you 'earn' your uberness depends on you but it always comes with a price. Now you may think the only 'fair' way to earn uberness is example 'a'. That is your opinion and you are welcome to it. But where exactly do you draw the line for integrity? How is someone who uses thier RL wealth to own 2-3 accounts and comps and PL thier toons up any better then someone who buys a made toon on Ebay? Is every use of RL cash to better your character immoral? Is it ok for someone to give me a Fungi tunic but if I buy one off Ebay is that wrong? What's the difference integrity wise if I did'nt 'earn' it?<br>
<br>
Playing with a lot of high end toons I have learned many of them take 'short cuts' to the top. Guess what? That is why they are at the top! That's how they got there before you and I. I don't hold anything against them, but that is definately the reason in a lot of cases. <br>
<br>
Of the big three guilds on FV I know of examples of all of them taking advantage of things you may consider questionable. You think AS is the only guild that cares about 'phat lewts' ? Wake up. These guilds are willing to make some sacrifices for success and that's what makes them successful. <br>
<br>
There is always a price for uberness, but it is up to each individual to determine what they are willing to pay. <br>
<br>
the Venerable John Falstaff<br>
