<br>
In otherwords, YOU being an ebay person does NOT demean me. This is a video game and in many ways, i'm only competing with myself (and maybe my work and class schedule). To think that one persons expediture of money somehow actually has some permanent affect on your psyche is to give other people far too much power.<br>
<br>
Heagan, I respect what you say, but I think you are giving other people too much input into your enjoyment of the game.<br>
<br>
Take some pride in what YOU do and don't worry so much about what other people are doing. No person is so full of integrity and honor that they can lash about randomly at any perceived dishonor or impropriety.<br>
<br>
As for the endgame... if you think the endgame is just about loot... you are in for QUITE a shock when you get there. The truth of the matter is that once you get to a certain point, almost every gear upgrade is a microfractional additional benefit. The effort put out to get that upgrade is rarely worth the benefit... however it IS worth the fun factor.<br>
<br>
The point of it is: you have a character who is well equipped and powerful... and you want to do something difficult but fun. This is why you hear so many people on high-visibility guild sites complaining about play balance. What they are REALLY talking about is how fun the encounter is. <p>Nakath<BR>
