Powerleveling and twinking are not violations of the EULA.<br>
eBaying and account sharing are violations of the EULA.<br>
The EULA is what we are all expected to follow. <br>
We have to agree to is everytime we log on.<br>
<br>
A person that levels 1-60 without violating the EULA has every right to feel cheapened when he has to deal with someone that 'bought' his level 60 character. It actually comes to affect the honest player when that player loses a roll on an item against an eBayer that shouldn't have been there in the first place.<br>
<br>
